<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="165" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1154</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-22"><hi rend="italic">November 22,
                                        1920</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received December 28.]</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 617</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm my
                                telegram No. 77, of November 20, 11 a.m.,<note n="27" xml:id="d165fn27">Not printed.</note> wherein I reported total
                                deposits to November 15, <pb facs="0293" n="203" xml:id="pg_203"/>
                                1920, on account of interest on Guayaquil &amp; Quito Railway bonds,
                                and salt certificates. The exact amount of those deposits is as
                                follows: <table cols="5" rend="width: 80%;" rendition="#center-block" rows="2">
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Account</cell>
                                        <cell>of</cell>
                                        <cell>interest</cell>
                                        <cell>on</cell>
                                        <cell>railway bonds, S/.260,343.17</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>“</cell>
                                        <cell>“</cell>
                                        <cell>“</cell>
                                        <cell>“</cell>
                                        <cell>salt certificates, 65,263.37</cell>
                                    </row>
                                </table></p>
                            <p>As stated in my telegram, no remittances have been made, but I was
                                informed on Saturday by Mr. Norton that the President of Ecuador had
                                informed him that the failure to make remittance of these monies is
                                due to the inability of the Government to buy exchange on London.
                                Mr. Norton advised me that the President had assured him that no
                                part of the sums deposited would be withdrawn, and that remittances
                                would be made as soon as drafts on London could be purchased.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chas. S.
                                Hartman</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>